@page "/product/ai"
@layout MarketingLayout

<PageTitle>AI Copilot &mdash; NavTour</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="NavTour AI Copilot drafts annotations, rewrites copy, reviews demos for quality, and scores buyer intent — all powered by Anthropic Claude." />
</HeadContent>

@* ── HERO ── *@
<section class="nt-page-hero">
    <div class="nt-container">
        <span class="eyebrow">AI Copilot</span>
        <h1>Your demo team,<br /><em>augmented by Claude.</em></h1>
        <p class="lead">NavTour AI drafts annotation copy, rewrites tooltip text, reviews demos for quality, and scores buyer intent — all powered by Anthropic Claude with a zero-training policy on your workspace content.</p>
        <div class="nt-hero-actions">
            <a href="/register" class="btn btn-orange btn-lg">Start building free &rarr;</a>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">Talk to the team</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

@* ── AI PRIVACY CALLOUT ── *@
<section class="nt-section">
    <div class="nt-container">
        <div class="nt-callout">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
            <div>
                <strong>AI by Anthropic Claude &middot; No training on your content &middot; Data retained 30 days</strong>
                <p>NavTour sends demo content to Claude only for in-session inference. Your workspace content is never used to train AI models. All prompts and outputs are deleted after 30 days.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

@* ── CAPABILITY FRAMES ── *@
<section class="nt-frames-section">
    <div class="nt-container">
        <div class="nt-section-head">
            <div>
                <span class="num"><b>&sect; 02</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;Capabilities</span>
                <h2>Three things AI does so<br /><em>you don&rsquo;t have to.</em></h2>
            </div>
            <div class="aside">AI handles the tedious layer — drafting, reviewing, and scoring. You keep the creative and strategic judgment.</div>
        </div>

        <article class="nt-frame-row">
            <div class="nt-frame-copy">
                <div class="num">01<span class="slash">/</span><span class="lbl">Draft</span></div>
                <h3>Annotation copy in one click, not one hour.</h3>
                <p>Point at any element on a captured frame and ask AI to write the tooltip. Claude reads the surrounding UI context and generates a concise, on-brand annotation that you can edit or accept as-is.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Headline + body generated from screen context</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>EN/ES bilingual output in one pass</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Tone adapts to your brand voice settings</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-frame-visual">
                <span class="nt-frame-cap">AI Copilot &middot; annotation draft</span>
                <div class="nt-frame-img">
                    <img src="/images/shots/editor.png" alt="AI drafting annotation copy in the editor" class="nt-lightbox" />
                </div>
                <div class="anno tl">
                    <div class="lbl">Powered by Claude</div>
                    <strong>Context-aware drafting</strong>
                    <p>AI reads the surrounding UI to write copy that fits — not generic filler.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        <article class="nt-frame-row reverse">
            <div class="nt-frame-copy">
                <div class="num">02<span class="slash">/</span><span class="lbl">Review</span></div>
                <h3>AI flags weak demos <em>before</em> they leave the editor.</h3>
                <p>Before you publish, the AI Reviewer scans your demo for common failure patterns: steps that are too long, missing CTAs, confusing branch logic, and copy that reads like a feature list instead of a benefit.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Quality score with actionable improvement notes</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Step-level feedback, not just global suggestions</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>One-click rewrites for flagged annotations</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-frame-visual">
                <span class="nt-frame-cap">AI Reviewer &middot; quality scan</span>
                <div class="nt-frame-img">
                    <img src="/images/shots/player-step1.png" alt="AI review scorecard for a demo" class="nt-lightbox" />
                </div>
                <div class="anno br">
                    <div class="lbl">Before you publish</div>
                    <strong>Catch weak steps early</strong>
                    <p>The review runs in seconds. Most demos ship cleaner on the first pass.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        <article class="nt-frame-row">
            <div class="nt-frame-copy">
                <div class="num">03<span class="slash">/</span><span class="lbl">Score</span></div>
                <h3>Intent signals that tell reps <em>who to call next.</em></h3>
                <p>AI watches demo engagement patterns — time on step, replay loops, CTA clicks — and surfaces an intent score for each lead. Pipe the score into HubSpot or Salesforce so reps act on signal, not intuition.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Per-viewer intent score in the analytics dashboard</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>CRM field sync for lead scoring workflows</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Slack alert when a high-intent lead re-views the demo</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-frame-visual">
                <span class="nt-frame-cap">Analytics &middot; intent scoring</span>
                <div class="nt-frame-img">
                    <img src="/images/shots/analytics.png" alt="Intent score dashboard" class="nt-lightbox" />
                </div>
                <div class="anno tr">
                    <div class="lbl">Signal, not noise</div>
                    <strong>Act on intent, not vanity</strong>
                    <p>Reps see who is ready for a call — not just who opened the link.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

